<paragraph blockId="20.[227,436,1515,1541]" box="[227,436,1515,1541]" pageId="20" pageNumber="155">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,436,1515,1541]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="155" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,436,1515,1541]" pageId="20" pageNumber="155">Shell description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[224,1436,1563,1664]" pageId="20" pageNumber="155">
PROTOCONCH (
<figureCitation box="[384,484,1563,1590]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[227,270,1967,1993]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-204@21.[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Anatoma paucisculpta sp. nov. A–C. Paratype (SMF 358993), INDEX19_104RO (I19_Ma_91). H 0.77 mm, W 0.99 mm, Ha 0.61 mm, Wp 0.20 mm. D–H. Holotype (SMF 358992), INDEX15_62R" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784125/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="155">Fig. 11F</figureCitation>
). One slightly elevated whorl, evenly rounded, sculpture small, irregularly oriented, straight or curved, short ridges; few spiral striae; smooth straight rim near margin; sharp flexuous lip, protrusion at periphery; transition to teleoconch clear by change in sculpture; diameter 
<quantity box="[1248,1356,1637,1664]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="20" pageNumber="155" unit="mm" value="0.21">0.21 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[226,1438,1704,2025]" lastBlockId="20.[227,1436,2036,2063]" pageId="20" pageNumber="155">
TELEOCONCH (
<figureCitation box="[387,528,1704,1731]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[227,270,1967,1993]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-204@21.[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Anatoma paucisculpta sp. nov. A–C. Paratype (SMF 358993), INDEX19_104RO (I19_Ma_91). H 0.77 mm, W 0.99 mm, Ha 0.61 mm, Wp 0.20 mm. D–H. Holotype (SMF 358992), INDEX15_62R" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784125/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="155">Fig. 11D–E</figureCitation>
). With elevated spire, swollen whorls with protruding margins of selenizone; with spiral cordlets; rounded aperture with slit; suture deep. Height 1.0 mm, width 
<quantity box="[1222,1317,1741,1768]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="20" pageNumber="155" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
, height of aperture 
<quantity box="[331,420,1778,1805]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="155" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
(70 % of total height); colour translucent grayish white. 2¼ regular whorls with convex shoulder area and rounded base, selenizone slightly above periphery. Teleoconch I from protoconch to start of selenizone: slightly more than one well-rounded whorl, descending below protoconch; smooth, with up to six spiral cordlets, numerous prosocline growth lines. Teleoconch II with selenizone: slightly more than one whorl; shoulder area with seven spiral cordlets at the lip margin; new weaker cordlets emerging between older ones. Margins of selenizone sharply protruding outwards; growth lines on external sides of selenizone; inside margins smooth; surface between margins smooth with curved growth lines (
<figureCitation box="[392,573,2036,2063]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[227,270,1967,1993]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-204@21.[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Anatoma paucisculpta sp. nov. A–C. Paratype (SMF 358993), INDEX19_104RO (I19_Ma_91). H 0.77 mm, W 0.99 mm, Ha 0.61 mm, Wp 0.20 mm. D–H. Holotype (SMF 358992), INDEX15_62R" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784125/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="155">Fig. 11B, E, H</figureCitation>
). Base body whorl smooth background with about 20 irregularly spaced
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,767,229,256]" box="[227,852,229,256]" lastBlockId="21.[447,852,230,256]" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">
<bibCitation box="[227,852,229,256]" journal="European Journal of Taxonomy" page="135" pageId="21" pageNumber="156" score="32.06971554747712" volume="826" year="2022">
<emphasis box="[227,597,229,256]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">European Journal of Taxonomy</emphasis>
826: 135–162 (2022)
</bibCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,1436,303,364]" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">
spiral cordlets and about 60 regular axial riblets; spiral and axial sculpture stronger in umbilical area (
<figureCitation box="[238,346,338,364]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[227,270,1967,1993]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-204@21.[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Anatoma paucisculpta sp. nov. A–C. Paratype (SMF 358993), INDEX19_104RO (I19_Ma_91). H 0.77 mm, W 0.99 mm, Ha 0.61 mm, Wp 0.20 mm. D–H. Holotype (SMF 358992), INDEX15_62R" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784125/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">Fig. 11G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,1436,403,465]" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">
UMBILICUS. Open, tortuous and deep; steep smoothly curved spiral keel ending at base of columellar callus (
<figureCitation box="[311,455,438,465]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[227,270,1967,1993]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-204@21.[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Anatoma paucisculpta sp. nov. A–C. Paratype (SMF 358993), INDEX19_104RO (I19_Ma_91). H 0.77 mm, W 0.99 mm, Ha 0.61 mm, Wp 0.20 mm. D–H. Holotype (SMF 358992), INDEX15_62R" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784125/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">Fig. 11D, G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,1437,504,707]" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">
APERTURE (
<figureCitation box="[361,474,504,531]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[227,270,1967,1993]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-204@21.[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Anatoma paucisculpta sp. nov. A–C. Paratype (SMF 358993), INDEX19_104RO (I19_Ma_91). H 0.77 mm, W 0.99 mm, Ha 0.61 mm, Wp 0.20 mm. D–H. Holotype (SMF 358992), INDEX15_62R" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784125/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
). With semi-circular rounded base, funnel-shaped towards selenizone, convex shoulder, pointed at union with penultimate whorl, well rounded on parietal and columellar side. Lip sharp; protruding, oblique on columella with minor rib joining in v-shape with columellar keel (
<figureCitation box="[235,346,610,636]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[227,270,1967,1993]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-204@21.[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Anatoma paucisculpta sp. nov. A–C. Paratype (SMF 358993), INDEX19_104RO (I19_Ma_91). H 0.77 mm, W 0.99 mm, Ha 0.61 mm, Wp 0.20 mm. D–H. Holotype (SMF 358992), INDEX15_62R" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784125/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">Fig. 11G</figureCitation>
); rounded towards base and parietal area with thin callus. Slit ¼ whorl deep with flattened sharp margins above and below, lip prosocline, union perpendicular to penultimate whorl (
<figureCitation box="[1316,1423,645,671]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[227,270,1967,1993]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-204@21.[227,1436,978,1924]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Anatoma paucisculpta sp. nov. A–C. Paratype (SMF 358993), INDEX19_104RO (I19_Ma_91). H 0.77 mm, W 0.99 mm, Ha 0.61 mm, Wp 0.20 mm. D–H. Holotype (SMF 358992), INDEX15_62R" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784125" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784125/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">Fig. 11E</figureCitation>
). Callus thin; inside aperture smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,519,745,771]" box="[227,519,745,771]" pageId="21" pageNumber="156">
