<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="157" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[227,341,535,561]" box="[227,341,535,561]" pageId="22" pageNumber="157">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,535,561]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="22" pageNumber="157" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,535,561]" pageId="22" pageNumber="157">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[227,1436,583,684]" pageId="22" pageNumber="157">
The lack of distinct and regular spiral and or axial sculpture is uncommon. The outline is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Herbert, 1963)" baseAuthorityName="Herbert" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[259,674,620,647]" class="Gastropoda" family="Anatomidae" genus="Anatoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="22" pageNumber="157" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="africanae">
<emphasis box="[259,484,620,647]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="157">Anatoma africanae</emphasis>
(Herbert, 1963)
</taxonomicName>
from the Gallieni Fracture Zone, south of 
<collectingCountry box="[1173,1315,620,646]" name="Madagascar" pageId="22" pageNumber="157">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
at a depth of 
<quantity box="[259,335,658,684]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="157" unit="m" value="400.0">400 m</quantity>
, but this species has a distinct and fine axial and spiral sculpture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
